the needle, right?

317
00:19:08,308 --> 00:19:09,381
O kay.

318
00:19:09,406 --> 00:19:13,902
And, brother, I just found
the fucking needle !

319
00:19:20,235 --> 00:19:21,781
How'd you find it?

320
00:19:21,806 --> 00:19:23,102
I put the word out
with patrol...

321
00:19:23,127 --> 00:19:24,853
You know, the whole
hide-in-plain-sight thing.

322
00:19:24,905 --> 00:19:28,302
Juan Pierre flagged this one
and called me.

323
00:19:28,335 --> 00:19:30,102
This is a busy street.
Anyone see the driver?

324
00:19:30,125 --> 00:19:33,381
The restaurant manager said it was here
when he opened up. Is this the one you saw?

325
00:19:34,705 --> 00:19:37,363
<i>I feel like a kid
at his own surprise party.

326
00:19:37,408 --> 00:19:39,100
<i>This is the same truck.

327
00:19:39,136 --> 00:19:42,001
It's hard to say.
It all happened so fast.

328
00:19:42,036 --> 00:19:45,532
Let's go on a nonforensic-geek
limb here and say that it is.

329
00:19:45,565 --> 00:19:46,760
Why is it still running?

330
00:19:49,106 --> 00:19:52,032
It keeps the back compartment
refrigerated.

331
00:19:59,208 --> 00:20:00,801
Dios mío.

332
00:20:01,735 --> 00:20:04,631
Holy shit,
they're fucking fingertips.

333
00:20:08,535 --> 00:20:10,903
Clean slices,
no blood.

334
00:20:13,937 --> 00:20:17,832
My guess is he drained the body entirely
before these cuts were made.

335
00:20:17,866 --> 00:20:19,733
How'd he do that?
Some kind of pump?

336
00:20:19,768 --> 00:20:21,033
No.

337
00:20:21,065 --> 00:20:24,433
I had forensics do a workup
on our last victim.

338
00:20:24,466 --> 00:20:26,401
Our guy's old school.

339
00:20:26,435 --> 00:20:29,002
Yeah, he hoists the body up,
severs the jugular.

340
00:20:29,038 --> 00:20:30,700
The heart does all the work.

341
00:20:30,736 --> 00:20:33,431
It's the most effective method,
really.

342
00:20:33,465 --> 00:20:35,700
Fucking butcher.

343
00:20:37,707 --> 00:20:40,661
<i>There are 206 bones
in the human body.

344
00:20:40,708 --> 00:20:43,902
<i>He could have left
any one of them.

345
00:20:43,938 --> 00:20:47,660
<i>But he gave us exactly what
we need to identify the victim,

346
00:20:47,708 --> 00:20:50,932
<i>like he's leaving a trail
of bread crumbs.

347
00:20:54,766 --> 00:20:56,061
Who made the find?

348
00:20:56,687 --> 00:20:57,970
Officer Morgan.

349
00:20:58,088 --> 00:21:00,243
Harry's daughter ?

350
00:21:00,256 --> 00:21:03,001
Must be in the genes,
her and her brother.

351
00:21:03,677 --> 00:21:05,241
This truck's a good get.

352
00:21:05,465 --> 00:21:06,703
It's their first solid lead.

353
00:21:06,716 --> 00:21:10,373
I encourage all my officers
to think outside the box.

354
00:21:10,387 --> 00:21:12,432
Well, nice work, lieutenant.

355
00:21:12,666 --> 00:21:14,301
I got the Deputy-Mayor.

356
00:21:14,536 --> 00:21:16,630
Congratulate Morgan for me.

357
00:21:27,705 --> 00:21:29,660
<i>Another beautiful Miami day -

358
00:21:29,707 --> 00:21:33,061
<i>Mutilated corpses with the
chance of afternoon shows.

359
00:21:33,106 --> 00:21:35,230
Chalk one up
for Miami metro, eh, ma'am?

360
00:21:35,267 --> 00:21:38,603
Last time I checked, Morgan,
I'm the lieutenant,

361
00:21:38,638 --> 00:21:43,463
which means my officers keep me
apprised at all times on all things.

362
00:21:43,506 --> 00:21:45,323
You pull a stunt like that again,

363
00:21:45,337 --> 00:21:47,201
it won't matter
who your father was.

364
00:21:47,298 --> 00:21:48,963
Okay?

365
00:22:16,965 --> 00:22:18,701
Dude, is this blood?

366
00:22:18,738 --> 00:22:21,532
It's chocolate.
It's on your shirt, too.

367
00:22:24,206 --> 00:22:26,402
It's a new shirt.

368
00:22:27,035 --> 00:22:28,863
What is taking so long?

369
00:22:28,905 --> 00:22:30,671
It's a big truck.

370
00:22:31,007 --> 00:22:33,860
<i>They won't find anything,
not even a Tic Tac.

371
00:22:33,907 --> 00:22:35,863
<i>He's thought all this through.

372
00:22:35,905 --> 00:22:38,333
<i>I know I would.

373
00:22:38,365 --> 00:22:40,202
Your famous hunches
telling you anything?

374
00:22:40,238 --> 00:22:41,602
Ice cold.

375
00:22:41,835 --> 00:22:43,360
You're a goddamn riot.

376
00:22:43,387 --> 00:22:44,732
This fucking guy's
toying with us.

377
00:22:45,078 --> 00:22:46,722
<i>Deb's right.

378
00:22:46,756 --> 00:22:49,592
<i>This truck's not another piece
of the puzzle...

379
00:22:49,667 --> 00:22:51,201
<i>...They are.

380
00:22:56,635 --> 00:22:58,501
Watching ice melt...
This is fun.

381
00:22:58,538 --> 00:23:01,233
Stand a little closer, Morgan,
and I'll melt your heart.

382
00:23:01,266 --> 00:23:03,500
I think he's got a crush
on you, Dex.

383
00:23:04,555 --> 00:23:06,773
Yo, I was talking to Morgan
the sister.

384
00:23:06,867 --> 00:23:08,803
Vince Masuka
only swings one way.

385
00:23:08,855 --> 00:23:10,062
Yeah,
from vine to vine.

386
00:23:10,105 --> 00:23:11,033
Enough.

387
00:23:11,067 --> 00:23:13,162
I'm glad to see the
sexual-harassment seminar

388
00:23:13,187 --> 00:23:14,610
really paid off.

389
00:23:30,435 --> 00:23:33,703
This is seriously
fucked-up, my friends.

390
00:23:35,135 --> 00:23:37,160
Why go to all this trouble?

391
00:23:37,597 --> 00:23:40,600
What's this sick son of a bitch
trying to tell us?

392
00:23:40,867 --> 00:23:43,330
<i>Not "us".
Me.

393
00:23:43,365 --> 00:23:47,901
<i>My freezer, the painted doll's
fingernails...

394
00:23:48,337 --> 00:23:51,532
<i>I think he's trying
to impress me...

395
00:23:51,665 --> 00:23:53,931
<i>And it's working.

396
00:23:54,265 --> 00:23:57,502
What, a man can't call his wife
three times in one day?

397
00:23:57,538 --> 00:23:59,703
Sí, claro.

398
00:23:59,738 --> 00:24:01,233
Bueno.

399
00:24:01,266 --> 00:24:04,302
Kiss my baby and tell her,
"daddy be home para la cena."

400
00:24:04,708 --> 00:24:06,833
I'm getting another call.

401
00:24:06,865 --> 00:24:08,160
Yeah, te amo.

402
00:24:09,206 --> 00:24:10,933
Batista.

403
00:24:10,966 --> 00:24:12,963
¿De veras?
I'll be there in two minutes.

404
00:24:15,905 --> 00:24:17,400
She's still in surgery.

405
00:24:17,438 --> 00:24:19,101
The doctors are hopeful.

406
00:24:19,137 --> 00:24:20,760
<i>Ice-truck killer returns,

407
00:24:20,775 --> 00:24:22,701
<i>dead undercover cop -

408
00:24:22,738 --> 00:24:24,862
<i>It's a typical day
in the neighborhood.

409
00:24:24,908 --> 00:24:26,860
You got to hear this.

410
00:24:29,706 --> 00:24:32,151
<i>Ricky, where the fuck are you?

411
00:24:32,168 --> 00:24:33,902
<i>I'm gonna try
for the back door.

412
00:24:33,936 --> 00:24:36,230
<i>Fuck, he saw me!

413
00:24:36,266 --> 00:24:38,701
<i>Please don't hurt me!

414
00:24:40,136 --> 00:24:41,400
Lieutenant!

415
00:24:41,438 --> 00:24:44,333
National database
kicked back the DNA match.

416
00:24:46,008 --> 00:24:47,530
Norberto Cervantes.

417
00:24:49,435 --> 00:24:51,552
Let me see that.

418
00:25:03,505 --> 00:25:05,003
Dame.
Ahora.

419
00:25:07,666 --> 00:25:09,501
Es tu día de mala suerte.

420
00:25:16,106 --> 00:25:19,362
Estoy agradecido
por tu lealdad.

421
00:25:19,405 --> 00:25:21,303
El gusto es mío, patrón.

422
00:25:27,205 --> 00:25:28,541
Police!
Put your hands up!

423
00:25:28,566 --> 00:25:30,161
Police!
Put your hands up!

424
00:25:31,185 --> 00:25:32,253
Get them down!

425
00:25:32,305 --> 00:25:34,530
Put your fucking hands up!
Put your hands up!

426
00:25:39,268 --> 00:25:40,533
Is that necessary?

427
00:25:40,565 --> 00:25:42,603
It's a dangerous world,
Guerrero.

428
00:25:44,935 --> 00:25:48,130
Yes, and one can't be
too careful, detective.

429
00:25:52,867 --> 00:25:55,060
Yes, I-I've had alc...

430
00:25:55,405 --> 00:25:57,830
...problems with alcohol
in the past.

431
00:25:57,868 --> 00:25:59,530
I never tried to hide that.

432
00:25:59,565 --> 00:26:03,263
But... you heard
from my A.A. sponsor.

433
00:26:03,308 --> 00:26:05,930
I- I've been sober
for over a year now.

434
00:26:07,468 --> 00:26:12,660
Look, I-I'm not disputing
that... that it was my car...

435
00:26:12,707 --> 00:26:15,032
that hit Mr. Pryce.

436
00:26:15,568 --> 00:26:17,730
But...

437
00:26:17,768 --> 00:26:22,131
I reported it stolen
hours before the accident.

438
00:26:26,467 --> 00:26:29,300
<i>Men like Matt Chambers know
how to pull on the invisible mask

439
00:26:29,325 --> 00:26:30,703
<i>of sympathy,

440
00:26:30,736 --> 00:26:32,433
<i>even empathy,

441
00:26:32,465 --> 00:26:36,301
<i>and otherwise right-thinking
people don't stand a chance.

442
00:26:43,035 --> 00:26:45,081
<i>"Not guilty."

443
00:26:45,636 --> 00:26:50,101
<i>Matt Chambers may have found
a way to beat the system...

444
00:26:50,137 --> 00:26:52,503
<i>...but so have I.

445
00:26:53,837 --> 00:26:56,062
Ricky, where the fuck are you?

446
00:26:56,105 --> 00:26:58,460
Fuck, he saw me.

447
00:26:58,505 --> 00:27:00,830
Please don't hurt me!

448
00:27:05,038 --> 00:27:06,803
The way we see it,

449
00:27:06,837 --> 00:27:09,753
you're in on the kill of Ricky Simmons,
but that's not enough for you

450
00:27:09,785 --> 00:27:11,543
or for Guerrero.

451
00:27:11,576 --> 00:27:14,011
Ricky is dead?

452
00:27:14,136 --> 00:27:15,800
That saddens me.

453
00:27:15,856 --> 00:27:17,663
Shut the fuck up!

454
00:27:22,467 --> 00:27:24,930
Wait, you're not implying

455
00:27:24,965 --> 00:27:27,000
that Ricky Simmons was a cop,
are you?

456
00:27:27,428 --> 00:27:29,601
I'm truly disappointed.

457
00:27:29,635 --> 00:27:32,161
Not only do I have a dead cop,

458
00:27:32,206 --> 00:27:35,830
someone broke in his house
and shot his wife.

459
00:27:35,867 --> 00:27:39,832
Word out in the world,
sergeant...

460
00:27:39,866 --> 00:27:42,202
Simmons's wife
was fucking around.

461
00:27:42,237 --> 00:27:45,961
Maybe he tried
to kill the bitch himself,

462
00:27:46,006 --> 00:27:48,701
and felt so bad about it,
he committed suicide.

463
00:27:48,806 --> 00:27:51,261
A cop murder-suicide...

464
00:27:51,807 --> 00:27:54,602
It's a health crisis
for you guys, ain't it?

465
00:27:56,036 --> 00:27:59,003
You think it's a fucking coincidence
your ass is in here?!

466
00:27:59,038 --> 00:28:02,382
