the morning Ricky Simmons died!

467
00:28:02,407 --> 00:28:03,603
Bullshit.

468
00:28:03,637 --> 00:28:05,461
We don't deal in bullshit.

469
00:28:05,507 --> 00:28:08,383
We deal in good police work...

470
00:28:08,406 --> 00:28:10,101
And good science.

471
00:28:15,708 --> 00:28:19,193
You must have been a
motherfucker at cat's cradle.

472
00:28:21,308 --> 00:28:22,863
I never played it.

473
00:28:22,907 --> 00:28:25,273
Okay, Kara Simmons was shot
while she was running.

474
00:28:25,288 --> 00:28:26,802
Her phone call
tells us that, right?

475
00:28:26,827 --> 00:28:29,601
And she was running towards
the back door... There.

476
00:28:29,618 --> 00:28:30,721
She turns.

477
00:28:30,738 --> 00:28:31,682
The shooter sees her.

478
00:28:31,706 --> 00:28:33,962
She's shot high on the chest.

479
00:28:34,007 --> 00:28:35,462
It spins her around,

480
00:28:35,507 --> 00:28:37,931
spraying blood on the walls
there... and there.

481
00:28:38,106 --> 00:28:39,701
She loses her cellphone.

482
00:28:39,736 --> 00:28:41,561
She struggles
with the coffee table,

483
00:28:41,605 --> 00:28:43,702
the couch, and then
she finally falls back,

484
00:28:43,738 --> 00:28:44,702
"Pop"... There.

485
00:28:50,238 --> 00:28:52,361
She never got this far.

486
00:28:54,538 --> 00:28:56,332
It's not her blood.

487
00:29:07,306 --> 00:29:09,462
Angel, meet our shooter.

488
00:29:11,308 --> 00:29:14,430
DNA of Cervantes' flesh
in Ricky Simmons' mouth.

489
00:29:14,468 --> 00:29:17,700
DNA from a rogue drop of blood
we found at the Simmons' house.

490
00:29:24,138 --> 00:29:25,862
Tell me you're sure about this.

491
00:29:25,906 --> 00:29:27,462
100%.

492
00:29:27,605 --> 00:29:29,891
That puts Cervantes
at both crime scenes.

493
00:29:29,907 --> 00:29:31,641
Let's nail his coffin
and ship it.

494
00:29:31,707 --> 00:29:32,803
Hang on, sergeant.

495
00:29:32,835 --> 00:29:34,722
We get him to roll
over on Guerrero

496
00:29:34,758 --> 00:29:36,043
and we own them both.

497
00:29:36,045 --> 00:29:38,060
You're talking
about throwing him a deal?

498
00:29:38,086 --> 00:29:39,151
And then, what ?
He walks?

499
00:29:39,175 --> 00:29:41,311
If he does, we pick him up
on other charges.

500
00:29:41,568 --> 00:29:43,790
If he gets us Guerrero,
it's win-win.

501
00:29:43,807 --> 00:29:45,602
Gets us Guerrero?!
We can't catch the guy.

502
00:29:45,637 --> 00:29:47,460
He's un-fucking-touchable!

503
00:29:47,505 --> 00:29:49,800
Come on, lieutenant.

504
00:29:49,836 --> 00:29:51,060
We already got a win.

505
00:29:51,087 --> 00:29:52,983
It's not about your win.

506
00:29:53,008 --> 00:29:55,262
It's about the big picture.

507
00:30:05,466 --> 00:30:07,461
<i>I've seen this before.

508
00:30:07,807 --> 00:30:10,233
<i>Whenever a cop is killed,
it's like everyone's life

509
00:30:10,268 --> 00:30:13,511
<i>has been stopped
in mid-sentence.

510
