00:48:08,678 --> 00:48:10,800
It's about the guy
who killed Davey, isn't it?

769
00:48:10,818 --> 00:48:14,241
The judge said the bust wasn't
righteous and let him walk.

770
00:48:15,218 --> 00:48:17,682
That guy kills a cop,
and nothing happens?

771
00:48:19,386 --> 00:48:20,880
That's not fair.

772
00:48:20,905 --> 00:48:22,650
Life's not fair, Dexter.

773
00:48:23,655 --> 00:48:25,321
Can't anyone do anything?

774
00:48:25,457 --> 00:48:27,361
Can't you do something?

775
00:48:28,486 --> 00:48:30,392
No, not now.

776
00:48:32,817 --> 00:48:34,412
So what, then?

777
00:48:34,457 --> 00:48:37,210
The world just keeps
spinning out of control?

778
00:48:39,356 --> 00:48:40,913
No.

779
00:48:41,658 --> 00:48:44,511
The world can always
be set right again.

780
00:48:45,318 --> 00:48:48,683
<i>That guy kills a cop,
and nothing happens?

781
00:48:48,718 --> 00:48:50,521
<i>Not anymore.

782
00:48:51,058 --> 00:48:52,783
Be back in a sec.

783
00:48:53,616 --> 00:48:55,781
I'm kind of running the gamut
here emotion-wise.

784
00:48:55,807 --> 00:48:57,532
Nature calls.

785
00:48:58,417 --> 00:49:01,943
<i>All the planning,
the making sure...

786
00:49:02,417 --> 00:49:04,292
<i>Does it go away
because I have a chance

787
00:49:04,317 --> 00:49:08,320
<i>to rid the world of a cop
killer and balance the books?

788
00:49:08,987 --> 00:49:10,012
<i>Do I just ignore

789
00:49:10,037 --> 00:49:12,921
<i>everything my father taught me
about how to do this right,

790
00:49:13,055 --> 00:49:16,751
<i>about how to stay safe
so I can do it again?

791
00:49:24,786 --> 00:49:26,443
Yep.

792
00:49:28,158 --> 00:49:31,212
I don't give a shit
about your goddamn problems.

793
00:49:31,257 --> 00:49:33,852
I gave you a job.
You take care of it.

794
00:49:37,615 --> 00:49:39,403
What the fuck
you looking at?

795
00:49:51,855 --> 00:49:54,202
<i>Happy birthday, Alex!
Rip right into it.

796
00:50:06,555 --> 00:50:08,283
<i>But next year
at this time...

797
00:50:08,315 --> 00:50:10,463
It's you.

798
00:50:10,755 --> 00:50:12,713
And you.

799
00:50:12,757 --> 00:50:15,782
<i>Thanks, dad.

800
00:50:18,815 --> 00:50:20,313
<i>All right,
enough corniness.

801
00:50:20,356 --> 00:50:22,313
We meet again...

802
00:50:30,185 --> 00:50:31,611
...for the last time.

803
00:50:34,415 --> 00:50:36,811
I didn't do anyth-
Anything.

804
00:50:36,855 --> 00:50:38,851
Some people believe that.

805
00:50:41,215 --> 00:50:42,673
The problem is, I don't.

806
00:50:43,085 --> 00:50:44,911
But it's true.

807
00:50:44,956 --> 00:50:46,450
I was - I was set up.

808
00:50:49,256 --> 00:50:50,652
By whom?

809
00:50:50,687 --> 00:50:54,111
That - That family.

810
00:50:55,458 --> 00:50:59,350
They needed someone to blame. It's a
natural thing to do when you're grieving.

811
00:50:59,415 --> 00:51:01,183
So then none of this
is your fault?

812
00:51:01,217 --> 00:51:02,750
I swear.

813
00:51:03,886 --> 00:51:06,050
Okay! Okay! Okay!
No!

814
00:51:06,088 --> 00:51:08,010
Okay. Okay. Stop.

815
00:51:08,056 --> 00:51:09,813
All right.

816
00:51:09,856 --> 00:51:11,011
Okay, okay.

817
00:51:11,057 --> 00:51:14,083
It - It was me,
only it wasn't me.

818
00:51:14,118 --> 00:51:15,981
It was the booze.

819
00:51:16,017 --> 00:51:18,253
It takes me over.

820
00:51:18,288 --> 00:51:21,780
That's a point of view to which
I'm not entirely unsympathetic.

821
00:51:22,235 --> 00:51:24,512
Neither you nor I

822
00:51:24,657 --> 00:51:28,910
is in complete control
of our destinies.

823
00:51:29,655 --> 00:51:31,283
Although, at the moment,

824
00:51:31,306 --> 00:51:32,882
it would seem
I have the upper hand.

825
00:51:34,518 --> 00:51:36,810
Really, I'm so sorry.

826
00:51:36,858 --> 00:51:39,340
You've done this
too many times to be sorry.

827
00:51:52,416 --> 00:51:55,961
<i>Carlos Guerrero has chosen
to live in a dangerous world.

828
00:51:56,017 --> 00:51:58,182
<i>That's his truth.

829
00:51:58,215 --> 00:51:59,950
<i>My truth is,

830
00:51:59,985 --> 00:52:02,881
<i>that world doesn't need me
to balance its books.

831
00:52:35,158 --> 00:52:40,510
<i>Matt Chambers, welcome to
your last change of address.

832
00:52:40,555 --> 00:52:42,352
<i>You'll like it here.

833
00:52:42,385 --> 00:52:45,382
<i>You and your neighbors
have so much in common.

834
00:53:12,358 --> 00:53:15,281
<i>The worst thing about finally
putting together a puzzle

835
00:53:15,816 --> 00:53:18,210
<i>is finding
there are missing pieces.

836
00:53:25,416 --> 00:53:28,652
<i>He came back and left nothing
behind but a message -

837
00:53:28,888 --> 00:53:30,650
<i>Come find me.

838
00:53:33,255 --> 00:53:34,882
<i>And I will.

839
00:53:37,245 --> 00:53:39,753
<i>There are no secrets in life,

840
00:53:40,108 --> 00:53:42,303
<i>just hidden truths

841
00:53:42,475 --> 00:53:45,053
<i>that lie beneath the surface.

842
